The proof relies on the explicit description of the unit of the adjunctions involved in the cohesive structure.
The unit of `Γ ⊣ codisc` (which is `adj₃`) at a sheaf `S` maps a section `s` over `Y` and a morphism `y : ⊤ ⟶ Y` (wrapped in `ULift`) to the restriction `s|_{y.down}` (a section over `⊤`).
The unit of `disc ⊣ Γ` (which is `adj₂`) at `X` maps `x : X` to the section `toSheafify(x)` over `⊤` in `disc X`.
The left hand side of the goal reduces to the restriction of `toSheafify(x)` (seen as a section over `Y`) along `y`. By the naturality of `toSheafify`, this is `toSheafify` of the restriction of `x`. Since `x` is from a constant presheaf, its restriction is `x`. Thus, both sides equal `toSheafify(x)` over `⊤`.

